1
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:41,240
♪In rain or shine♪

2
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:46,870
♪When you're around,
the sun shines through♪

3
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Spare ourselves the endless thoughts
and guessing games♪

4
00:00:52,930 --> 00:00:58,880
♪Let's just meet
and escape these frames♪

5
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:02,600
♪I stand within the shadows deep♪

6
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:08,030
♪My hand outstretched,
your rescue I keep♪

7
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:12,850
♪Even if the world falls apart♪

8
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:15,870
♪No distance is too far♪

9
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:21,390
♪To stop us from coming together♪

10
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:27,710
♪Through the night,
you're at the end of the line♪

11
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:32,730
♪To protect you is my humble wish♪

12
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:36,920
♪Farewell, to the timid soul I knew♪

13
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,550
♪It was you who made me brave and new♪

14
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:46,180
=Always Home=
(Adapted from Xiao Ge's novel, Always Home)

15
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:49,180
=Episode 9=
(Go! Strive For Your Dream)

16
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:51,480
(Tianhe No.1 Middle School
welcomes you!)

17
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:54,670
(Life in the second year
of high school seems calm.)

18
00:01:54,860 --> 00:01:57,500
(But in reality, there are
turbulent undercurrents.)

19
00:01:58,420 --> 00:02:01,419
(Exams and papers are like monsters
with a huge appetite,)

20
00:02:01,420 --> 00:02:03,900
(always showing up right on time.)

21
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:07,420
(It swallows all the space
in your mind.)

22
00:02:11,980 --> 00:02:14,470
(As for Qi Qi and I,)

23
00:02:17,050 --> 00:02:19,190
(we still haven't reconciled.)

24
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:23,870
(Those emotions that can't be explained)

25
00:02:24,170 --> 00:02:26,500
(slowly get buried by time.)

26
00:02:26,850 --> 00:02:29,330
(I just hope that this time,
the teacher setting the questions)

27
00:02:29,330 --> 00:02:31,500
(won't put too much thought into it.)

28
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:33,820
(Also buried)

29
00:02:34,330 --> 00:02:36,030
(are my dreams.)

30
00:02:36,730 --> 00:02:38,289
(We've come across)

31
00:02:38,290 --> 00:02:40,710
(this essay topic
since elementary school.)

32
00:02:41,220 --> 00:02:43,620
(It feels like a descending curve,)

33
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:46,270
(less and less mentioned.)

34
00:02:47,010 --> 00:02:49,900
(In the end,
no one talks about it anymore.)

35
00:02:51,860 --> 00:02:54,270
(Because everyone starts
to care about their face.)

36
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,340
(We realize how hard it is)

37
00:02:56,540 --> 00:02:59,550
(to achieve your dreams.)

38
00:03:08,420 --> 00:03:10,190
Chen Huan'er, can I use your computer?

39
00:03:10,540 --> 00:03:12,150
Don't touch my computer.

40
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,550
What are you doing?

41
00:03:20,140 --> 00:03:21,710
Sports University?

42
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:23,880
How come you're suddenly

43
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:26,120
(Undergraduate admission scores inquiry)
paying attention to the exam?

44
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,980
(of Sports University of Jing City)
Just wanted to try it.

45
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:28,780
You and Song

46
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:31,480
have no worries about getting
into a good university in a big city.

47
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:32,590
Right now,

48
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:35,480
I'm actually a little worried
I won't get into any school.

49
00:03:36,010 --> 00:03:37,449
That wouldn't happen.

50
00:03:37,450 --> 00:03:39,620
If not, you could work in the city.

51
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:41,100
Or we could support you.

52
00:03:42,490 --> 00:03:44,500
You really think I can't support myself?

53
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:46,080
I want to get into the Sports University

54
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:47,540
because it's my dream to play soccer.

55
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:49,540
I get my goal in roundabout way, okay?

56
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:57,169
It would be so great
if I were like you and knew

57
00:03:57,170 --> 00:03:58,940
what I wanted to do from a young age.

58
00:03:59,770 --> 00:04:01,380
Then I wouldn't need to think so much.

59
00:04:01,610 --> 00:04:02,710
It'd be much easier.

60
00:04:04,730 --> 00:04:06,660
Otherwise, you could
just study agriculture.

61
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:08,100
That mysterious herb you have

62
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:09,780
seems to work well
for treating diarrhea.

63
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:10,840
I think you have a talent.

64
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:12,800
And your family has a history.
Isn't that great?

65
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:15,819
My family's connection is
with Traditional Chinese Medicine.

66
00:04:15,820 --> 00:04:17,500
That's also related to pharmacy.

67
00:04:17,810 --> 00:04:20,060
The field you're talking about
is agriculture,

68
00:04:20,340 --> 00:04:21,310
bro.

69
00:04:24,930 --> 00:04:25,979
Don't disturb me anymore.

70
00:04:25,980 --> 00:04:27,430
I'm still calculating the scores.

71
00:04:30,290 --> 00:04:30,929
Gosh.

72
00:04:30,930 --> 00:04:32,500
Why are they all so high?

73
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:35,580
Why don't you go home and calculate?

74
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:37,060
If I could go home and calculate,

75
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:38,280
I wouldn't be racking my brains

76
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:39,690
in this little shabby room of yours.

77
00:04:39,730 --> 00:04:41,560
Your house doesn't even
have a game console.

78
00:04:41,860 --> 00:04:44,219
Later, I'll lend you my PSP.
You can have it for two days.

79
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:46,240
You should practice more
since you're such a noob.

80
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:48,140
And you're still thinking
about playing games?

81
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:49,870
Move aside.

82
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:51,190
Let me check.

83
00:04:51,370 --> 00:04:52,129
Go ahead and check.

84
00:04:52,130 --> 00:04:53,350
I've already lost all hope.

85
00:05:02,062 --> 00:05:06,620
(Pharmacy program introduction)

86
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:19,940
(Student Transcript, Chen Huan'er)

87
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:26,260
Mom.

88
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:28,020
Don't look at it.

89
00:05:28,170 --> 00:05:30,580
I really didn't do well this time.

90
00:05:31,130 --> 00:05:32,160
I'm very satisfied.

91
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:34,060
According to your school's
first-tier status,

92
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:35,280
you can get into college.

93
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:36,870
I'm very content.

94
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:38,990
Mom,

95
00:05:39,290 --> 00:05:41,249
can't you have a little
more expectation for me?

96
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:42,620
A little more hope?

97
00:05:44,690 --> 00:05:47,019
I use encouragement-based education.

98
00:05:47,020 --> 00:05:49,020
Do you want me
to be like Li Tian's family?

99
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:51,820
Be grateful for the things you have.

100
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:52,620
Here.

101
00:05:53,810 --> 00:05:56,029
Mom, our teacher said

102
00:05:56,030 --> 00:05:58,290
I'm good at biology and chemistry.

103
00:05:58,370 --> 00:05:59,940
What about I studying pharmacy

104
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:01,430
in the future?

105
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:05,230
Think it over.

106
00:06:06,690 --> 00:06:07,779
Mom!

107
00:06:07,780 --> 00:06:10,100
Didn't you and Dad say
as long as I don't study medicine

108
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:11,180
I can study whatever I want?

109
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:14,230
Huan'er, pharmacy is
closely related to medicine.

110
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:16,910
Pharmacy might even be harder
than studying medicine.

111
00:06:17,100 --> 00:06:18,489
A girl

112
00:06:18,490 --> 00:06:20,430
should choose an easier major.

113
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:24,099
If this isn't okay, and that's not okay,

114
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:26,049
then what's the difference between me

115
00:06:26,050 --> 00:06:27,580
and a salted fish without dreams?

116
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:29,779
Isn't the salted fish just fine?

117
00:06:29,780 --> 00:06:31,940
You see, there's a whole wall
of them at home.

118
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:36,779
I'm full, Mom.

119
00:06:36,780 --> 00:06:38,230
I'm going out for a walk.

120
00:06:38,490 --> 00:06:39,670
Aren't you eating?

121
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:42,019
I'm a salted fish.

122
00:06:42,020 --> 00:06:43,820
I don't deserve to eat.

123
00:06:46,460 --> 00:06:48,020
Nothing wrong with a salted fish.

124
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,310
Li Tian?

125
00:07:08,930 --> 00:07:10,910
What's your problem?

126
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:12,500
You're the problem.

127
00:07:14,420 --> 00:07:15,910
What are you standing here for?

128
00:07:16,130 --> 00:07:17,419
This isn't your block's hallway.

129
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:18,310
Why do you care?

130
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:20,120
Earlier, you said
if Song Cong came in second,

131
00:07:20,130 --> 00:07:21,350
it would be like getting first.

132
00:07:21,420 --> 00:07:22,609
So what's going on now?

133
00:07:22,610 --> 00:07:24,020
You can't even keep second place.

134
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:25,460
So what do you want me to do?

135
00:07:25,580 --> 00:07:26,899
I already tried my best,

136
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:27,579
okay?

137
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:28,680
I went to study with him

138
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,350
because I was afraid
he wouldn't learn it.

139
00:07:30,350 --> 00:07:32,380
Don't question me
when you're raising the kid.

140
00:07:32,380 --> 00:07:33,620
Shouldn't it be me asking you?

141
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:34,320
No matter what,

142
00:07:34,380 --> 00:07:35,910
I just care about the result.

143
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:43,539
This hallway has poor soundproofing.

144
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:44,929
He's a boy.

145
00:07:44,930 --> 00:07:46,419
I don't want to say too much.

146
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:47,870
But isn't it obvious enough?

147
00:07:47,930 --> 00:07:48,899
Spending so much money,

148
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:51,100
going through all this effort,
and he still can't learn?

149
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:51,900
What's the reason?

150
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:52,810
It's because he's dumb.

151
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:53,899
If this continues,

152
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,660
he might as well transfer
to the art stream.

153
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:56,900
Third place is considered dumb?

154
00:07:59,580 --> 00:08:00,500
What?

155
00:08:01,810 --> 00:08:02,859
If you go back in,

156
00:08:02,860 --> 00:08:04,380
you'll be digging your own grave.

157
00:08:10,980 --> 00:08:12,060
What then?

158
00:08:29,340 --> 00:08:30,419
No thanks.

159
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:31,870
I'm going back in a bit.

160
00:08:32,460 --> 00:08:34,219
I didn't bring it specifically for you.

161
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:35,670
I didn't eat enough at dinner.

162
00:08:42,610 --> 00:08:43,580
Thanks.

163
00:08:50,370 --> 00:08:51,179
Just now,

164
00:08:51,180 --> 00:08:52,979
my parents were having
a study discussion

165
00:08:52,980 --> 00:08:54,219
regarding my studies.

166
00:08:54,220 --> 00:08:55,729
My whole family are ace students.

167
00:08:55,730 --> 00:08:57,609
It's normal to have such discussions.

168
00:08:57,610 --> 00:08:58,699
You wouldn't get it.

169
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:00,310
So don't spread gossip.

170
00:09:01,010 --> 00:09:02,460
What's there to gossip about?

171
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:04,550
Your family isn't the center
of the universe.

172
00:09:04,580 --> 00:09:06,790
Besides, last time we...

173
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:08,670
Don't mention last time.

174
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:18,249
You did well enough to get third.

175
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:19,729
You know when I did poorly in exams,

176
00:09:19,730 --> 00:09:20,910
I used to tell myself,

177
00:09:21,010 --> 00:09:23,099
that the sun would still rise tomorrow.

178
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:26,220
I still have to get up,
eat, and go to school.

179
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:27,670
Life has to go on.

180
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:29,670
I'm not like you.

181
00:09:29,820 --> 00:09:31,060
For me,

182
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:32,310
scores are my life.

183
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,720
The ranking in exams determines
whether you win or lose.

184
00:09:34,730 --> 00:09:36,790
If I can't get first,
it's like waiting to die.

185
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:42,100
Looks like I have shallow knowledge.

186
00:09:42,220 --> 00:09:44,360
I just don't understand
the worries of top students.

187
00:09:44,370 --> 00:09:45,409
Of course,

188
00:09:45,410 --> 00:09:47,100
you've never even
made it to the top ten,

189
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:49,220
so you wouldn't know
the feeling of falling down.

190
00:09:58,580 --> 00:10:00,390
Can I ask you a question?

191
00:10:01,580 --> 00:10:02,310
Shoot.

192
00:10:03,410 --> 00:10:05,299
How did you get 45 points

193
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:07,060
on that essay?

194
00:10:08,770 --> 00:10:09,670
What's wrong with that?

195
00:10:09,890 --> 00:10:10,910
How much did you score?

196
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:15,529
29.

197
00:10:15,530 --> 00:10:16,670
29?

198
00:10:17,940 --> 00:10:19,099
Did you go off-topic?

199
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:20,550
I didn't go off-topic.

200
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:21,889
My dream is

201
00:10:21,890 --> 00:10:24,150
"a happy life in the midst
of ordinariness."

202
00:10:24,370 --> 00:10:25,940
That's not off-topic?

203
00:10:28,460 --> 00:10:29,430
Was it?

204
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:32,940
So, what was your essay topic?

205
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:34,529
"Keep your feet on the ground,

206
00:10:34,530 --> 00:10:35,769
look up at the stars,

207
00:10:35,770 --> 00:10:38,460
and do your best to make
the world a better place."

208
00:10:39,890 --> 00:10:41,580
Is that really your dream?

209
00:10:42,220 --> 00:10:43,580
Didn't I say this long ago?

210
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:45,820
My goal is to go abroad
for a "gold-plated" degree,

211
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:47,930
and follow the elite path
to become a winner in life.

212
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:50,310
I'm not talking about
predicting exam questions.

213
00:10:50,530 --> 00:10:51,699
I'm asking,

214
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,390
do you really think this way?

215
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,980
As long as the score is high,
that's all that matters.

216
00:11:02,980 --> 00:11:04,460
Besides, why should I tell you?

217
00:11:04,770 --> 00:11:05,790
I'm heading home now.

218
00:11:18,890 --> 00:11:19,980
Song Cong,

219
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:21,190
come here for a moment.

220
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:23,760
What is it?

221
00:11:23,770 --> 00:11:25,220
I got this from a colleague.

222
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:26,099
Their kid used it

223
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,700
to prepare for last year's Gaokao.

224
00:11:28,650 --> 00:11:30,099
Since you're staying in the country,

225
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:32,579
you'll definitely be aiming
for either Yenching or Huaqing.

226
00:11:32,580 --> 00:11:34,339
Both schools have excellent

227
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:35,409
economics programs.

228
00:11:35,410 --> 00:11:36,459
Which independent admission

229
00:11:36,460 --> 00:11:37,910
do you want to prepare for?

230
00:11:38,010 --> 00:11:39,889
Of course, you'll get in anyway.

231
00:11:39,890 --> 00:11:40,489
But...

232
00:11:40,490 --> 00:11:41,220
Mom.

233
00:11:41,770 --> 00:11:43,310
I'm only in Year 2.

234
00:11:43,530 --> 00:11:44,699
Isn't it a bit too early?

235
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:46,000
The Independent Admission Exams

236
00:11:46,020 --> 00:11:47,400
for these schools are different.

237
00:11:47,410 --> 00:11:48,699
You need to prepare in advance.

238
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:50,670
It'd be too late if you do it later.

239
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:53,860
Oh no.

240
00:11:53,940 --> 00:11:54,820
What is it?

241
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:55,970
I suddenly remembered

242
00:11:55,980 --> 00:11:57,310
Xichi asking to meet up.

243
00:11:58,820 --> 00:12:00,310
I better get going.

244
00:12:00,980 --> 00:12:02,649
It's late. What could be so important?

245
00:12:02,650 --> 00:12:04,030
I almost forgot.

246
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,550
This is more important.

247
00:12:05,610 --> 00:12:07,009
Get home soon.

248
00:12:07,010 --> 00:12:07,979
Yeah, will do.

249
00:12:07,980 --> 00:12:08,740
Okay.

250
00:12:15,580 --> 00:12:17,390
Bu, pass the ball!

251
00:12:19,580 --> 00:12:20,460
Yeah.

252
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:36,940
Jing Xichi.

253
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:39,940
How come you two came together?

254
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:46,459
What's up

255
00:12:46,460 --> 00:12:47,510
with you two?

256
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,220
- Taking a breath.
- Releasing stress.

257
00:12:55,060 --> 00:12:56,060
Good timing.

258
00:12:56,220 --> 00:12:57,820
I have something to announce.

259
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:00,009
I'm going to represent our school

260
00:13:00,010 --> 00:13:02,409
in the inter-high school soccer league.

261
00:13:02,410 --> 00:13:03,819
That's awesome.

262
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:05,600
It's your chance
to make the school proud.

263
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,700
Of course.

264
00:13:07,340 --> 00:13:09,489
I heard the coach
from Sport University will be there.

265
00:13:09,490 --> 00:13:10,489
Congrats!

266
00:13:10,490 --> 00:13:12,220
You're one step closer to your dream.

267
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:14,460
We'll see.

268
00:13:17,730 --> 00:13:18,580
Pass the ball!

269
00:13:28,860 --> 00:13:31,060
(I'm sure Song Cong is like me.)

270
00:13:31,650 --> 00:13:32,729
(Sometimes,)

271
00:13:32,730 --> 00:13:34,790
(I am so envious of Jing Xichi.)

272
00:13:35,370 --> 00:13:37,489
(He's always able
to talk about his dream)

273
00:13:37,490 --> 00:13:39,100
(so easily.)

274
00:13:39,980 --> 00:13:41,310
