280
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:03,150
Everyone,

281
00:14:03,460 --> 00:14:05,630
it's okay if the experiment fails.

282
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:06,649
The important things

283
00:14:06,650 --> 00:14:07,740
are that we have to remember

284
00:14:07,860 --> 00:14:10,060
the steps and test points.

285
00:14:10,220 --> 00:14:12,529
Knowing what to write during the exam

286
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:13,790
is key.

287
00:14:14,010 --> 00:14:16,339
To observe the Tyndall effect

288
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:17,979
more clearly,

289
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:19,030
first of all,

290
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:20,219
we need to produce

291
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:22,940
a colloidal substance
that meets the requirements.

292
00:14:23,820 --> 00:14:24,729
Jing Xichi!

293
00:14:24,730 --> 00:14:26,430
Anymore mischief
and you're out of here!

294
00:14:27,820 --> 00:14:29,409
During the experiment,

295
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:30,859
we need to carefully observe

296
00:14:30,860 --> 00:14:32,889
the state of different liquids

297
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:33,980
after mixing.

298
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:36,910
We should conduct the experiment
while taking notes.

299
00:14:37,370 --> 00:14:39,609
As you work on the experiment,

300
00:14:39,610 --> 00:14:41,009
I want to emphasize...

301
00:14:41,010 --> 00:14:42,059
This is pretty cool.

302
00:14:42,060 --> 00:14:43,630
Another important test point.

303
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:45,459
Magic...

304
00:14:45,460 --> 00:14:46,889
The magnitude of the Tyndall effect

305
00:14:46,890 --> 00:14:49,270
is influenced by several factors,

306
00:14:49,410 --> 00:14:50,550
including

307
00:14:50,650 --> 00:14:54,459
the intermolecular forces
between the solute and the solvent.

308
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:55,430
Jing Xichi!

309
00:14:59,770 --> 00:15:00,609
As well as

310
00:15:00,610 --> 00:15:04,430
the molar ratio of solute to solvent.

311
00:15:05,060 --> 00:15:06,939
The stronger the interaction

312
00:15:06,940 --> 00:15:09,030
between the solute and the solvent,

313
00:15:09,220 --> 00:15:11,339
the Tyndall effect we observe

314
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:13,889
will be more pronounced

315
00:15:13,890 --> 00:15:15,609
after we complete the experiment.

316
00:15:15,610 --> 00:15:18,299
When the number
of molecules is the same,

317
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:20,699
the lower the molar ratio of the solute,

318
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:22,009
the weaker

319
00:15:22,010 --> 00:15:24,579
the Tyndall effect we observe

320
00:15:24,580 --> 00:15:25,769
after the experiment.

321
00:15:25,770 --> 00:15:26,529
Therefore,

322
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:28,670
when conducting the experiment,

323
00:15:29,010 --> 00:15:30,430
pay close attention

324
00:15:30,610 --> 00:15:33,910
to the molar ratio
between the solute and the solvent.

325
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,219
This is the key

326
00:15:35,220 --> 00:15:37,219
to achieving the desired
experimental results.

327
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:38,220
Sorry about that.

