00:24:23,020 --> 00:24:25,320
but it's not childish
doing an impromptu speech today?

562
00:24:26,130 --> 00:24:27,590
It was made clear.

563
00:24:27,650 --> 00:24:29,969
Talk about your favorite thing, right?

564
00:24:29,970 --> 00:24:31,460
You just had to like it.

565
00:24:32,650 --> 00:24:33,940
Did you grow taller?

566
00:24:33,970 --> 00:24:35,390
Keep your hands to yourself.

567
00:24:38,220 --> 00:24:39,850
What was your speech about just now?

568
00:24:39,860 --> 00:24:41,500
I thought you understood.

569
00:24:44,060 --> 00:24:45,689
Yes, I understood.

570
00:24:45,690 --> 00:24:46,609
I wanted to check

571
00:24:46,610 --> 00:24:48,630
if he used proper language.

572
00:24:52,300 --> 00:24:53,460
Are you feeling better?

573
00:24:53,820 --> 00:24:54,870
Much better.

574
00:24:55,210 --> 00:24:56,670
Thanks for today.

575
00:24:57,170 --> 00:24:57,859
No worries.

576
00:24:57,860 --> 00:24:58,900
(Convenience Store)

577
00:24:59,130 --> 00:25:00,369
If not for you,

578
00:25:00,370 --> 00:25:02,540
I might not have been able
to sit for the test.

579
00:25:02,610 --> 00:25:03,590
It's nothing.

580
00:25:03,930 --> 00:25:04,689
Come, quick.

581
00:25:04,690 --> 00:25:05,980
Are you buying something?

582
00:25:12,100 --> 00:25:13,299
You're eating all these?

583
00:25:13,300 --> 00:25:14,150
Daughter.

584
00:25:15,860 --> 00:25:16,910
It's you.

585
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:19,169
Are you two classmates?

586
00:25:19,170 --> 00:25:20,539
We're deskmates.

587
00:25:20,540 --> 00:25:21,820
Deskmates? What a coincidence.

588
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,300
Here, take some more.

589
00:25:23,650 --> 00:25:24,259
Hello, sir.

590
00:25:24,260 --> 00:25:25,420
Dad, can you get me a bag?

591
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:25,830
Okay.

592
00:25:27,260 --> 00:25:28,670
That's your father?

593
00:25:29,370 --> 00:25:30,409
Do you remember?

594
00:25:30,410 --> 00:25:31,680
When you first got transferred,

595
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:32,360
I told you

596
00:25:32,380 --> 00:25:33,400
that I met you before.

597
00:25:33,580 --> 00:25:34,700
How much?

598
00:25:35,210 --> 00:25:36,300
Ten yuan.

599
00:25:37,260 --> 00:25:38,540
It was right here.

600
00:25:39,340 --> 00:25:40,220
Is that so?

601
00:25:40,340 --> 00:25:40,609
Here.

602
00:25:40,610 --> 00:25:42,020
Put the things inside.

603
00:25:43,060 --> 00:25:44,859
Sir, I can't eat all of these.

604
00:25:44,860 --> 00:25:45,649
It's fine.

605
00:25:45,650 --> 00:25:46,540
Take it.

606
00:25:48,740 --> 00:25:49,730
I should pay for these.

607
00:25:49,740 --> 00:25:50,910
No need.

608
00:25:51,780 --> 00:25:52,830
Just take it.

609
00:25:54,610 --> 00:25:55,910
Thank you.

610
00:25:56,780 --> 00:25:57,590
I'm off.

611
00:26:06,020 --> 00:26:07,689
Jing Xichi, what is going on?

612
00:26:07,690 --> 00:26:09,070
Li Tian is competing today...

613
00:26:11,890 --> 00:26:13,129
Li Tian?

614
00:26:13,130 --> 00:26:14,350
How did the test go?

615
00:26:16,580 --> 00:26:18,260
She obviously didn't do well.

616
00:26:18,610 --> 00:26:20,129
That's no way to speak to Miss Chen.

617
00:26:20,130 --> 00:26:21,830
What happened today was her idea.

618
00:26:22,580 --> 00:26:23,740
Come on, bro.

619
00:26:23,970 --> 00:26:24,830
Come.

620
00:26:25,610 --> 00:26:26,630
Sit down, please.

621
00:26:26,890 --> 00:26:28,940
Enough with the act, Jing Xichi.

622
00:26:29,210 --> 00:26:30,969
It's English. Good, good!

623
00:26:30,970 --> 00:26:32,760
Go on and talk in English
the whole day then.

624
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:33,980
Sure, I can.

625
00:26:34,970 --> 00:26:36,590
Look, TV.

626
00:26:36,890 --> 00:26:38,110
I like Television.

627
00:26:38,740 --> 00:26:40,190
Bro, cheers.

628
00:26:40,410 --> 00:26:41,430
Where's mine?

629
00:26:44,340 --> 00:26:45,350
Sorry.

630
00:26:46,580 --> 00:26:49,220
I don't know you come...

631
00:26:49,780 --> 00:26:51,300
So you forgot?

632
00:26:51,340 --> 00:26:52,019
Yes.

633
00:26:52,020 --> 00:26:52,859
Okay.

634
00:26:52,860 --> 00:26:54,500
But, there's water in the kitchen.

635
00:26:56,780 --> 00:26:58,330
(Tianhe No.1 Middle School
welcomes you!)

636
00:26:58,340 --> 00:26:59,780
This time, only Du Man from our class

637
00:26:59,780 --> 00:27:00,910
made it to the finals.

638
00:27:01,060 --> 00:27:02,609
If only Song Cong had participated.

639
00:27:02,610 --> 00:27:05,000
Yeah, Song Cong definitely would
have made it if he had gone.

640
00:27:05,260 --> 00:27:06,129
A bit of a shame.

641
00:27:06,130 --> 00:27:07,020
Yeah...

642
00:27:07,170 --> 00:27:07,940
Morning.

643
00:27:08,210 --> 00:27:09,499
Li Tian, congratulations!

644
00:27:09,500 --> 00:27:11,660
You won first place
in the English speech competition.

645
00:27:14,410 --> 00:27:15,670
Congrats, Li Tian!

646
00:27:21,210 --> 00:27:23,190
You are welcome.

647
00:27:34,130 --> 00:27:35,770
(7th "Tianhe Elegance Cup")

648
00:27:35,771 --> 00:27:38,180
(English Speech Competition.
First Prize: Li Tian)

649
00:27:41,300 --> 00:27:43,259
What's the point
of bringing this back to me?

650
00:27:43,260 --> 00:27:44,780
It's not even useful as a paperweight.

651
00:27:44,780 --> 00:27:46,880
Does it give extra points
for independent admissions?

652
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:49,090
At the very least, my English is great.

653
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:50,460
When I go abroad in the future,

654
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:51,660
I want to study English.

655
00:27:51,660 --> 00:27:53,320
You're getting more ridiculous
by the day.

656
00:27:53,320 --> 00:27:55,200
Am I sending you abroad
to study English?

657
00:27:55,210 --> 00:27:56,620
Does that even need to be studied?

658
00:27:56,620 --> 00:27:57,400
Of course, it does!

659
00:27:57,410 --> 00:27:58,200
In English studies,

660
00:27:58,200 --> 00:27:59,660
there's also English Literature major.

661
00:27:59,660 --> 00:28:02,129
The world is a global village now.
English is just a tool.

662
00:28:02,130 --> 00:28:04,259
Everyone can say at least
a few words in English.

663
00:28:04,260 --> 00:28:05,430
What a lack of ambition!

664
00:28:05,780 --> 00:28:06,969
This is my life.

665
00:28:06,970 --> 00:28:08,929
I have the right to choose my major.

666
00:28:08,930 --> 00:28:10,299
It's none of your business.

667
00:28:10,300 --> 00:28:11,350
What did you say?

668
00:28:11,580 --> 00:28:13,190
Say that to me again if you dare!

669
00:28:16,020 --> 00:28:17,540
What did he mean?

670
00:28:18,820 --> 00:28:20,169
Aren't you good at English?

671
00:28:20,170 --> 00:28:21,630
Why are you asking me?

672
00:28:21,970 --> 00:28:23,169
He spoke too fast.

673
00:28:23,170 --> 00:28:24,614
I didn't catch it.

674
00:28:24,615 --> 00:28:26,299
(Mastership lies in
excellence and honesty)

675
00:28:26,300 --> 00:28:27,150
Have water.

676
00:28:34,410 --> 00:28:36,190
Come, try this.

677
00:28:36,260 --> 00:28:37,350
It's really sweet.

678
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:41,220
Yeah, it is.

679
00:28:41,610 --> 00:28:42,740
Then eat more.

680
00:28:43,450 --> 00:28:44,300
That's enough.

681
00:28:46,450 --> 00:28:47,590
Actually,

682
00:28:48,130 --> 00:28:49,220
taking part

683
00:28:49,450 --> 00:28:50,739
in competitions

684
00:28:50,740 --> 00:28:52,540
is all about participation.

685
00:28:52,580 --> 00:28:54,220
Winning or not doesn't really matter.

686
00:28:54,580 --> 00:28:56,260
Mom, what are you talking about?

687
00:28:56,410 --> 00:28:57,369
Listen up.

688
00:28:57,370 --> 00:29:00,129
I'm very likely to win an award
in this competition.

689
00:29:00,130 --> 00:29:01,099
I've made up my mind.

690
00:29:01,100 --> 00:29:02,449
I want to study pharmacy.

691
00:29:02,450 --> 00:29:04,220
I'll still do it
even if it's exhausting.

692
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:05,700
What nonsense are you talking about?

693
00:29:08,210 --> 00:29:09,500
What's wrong?

694
00:29:09,930 --> 00:29:10,910
It's nothing.

695
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:13,190
I just have a bit of a stomachache.

696
00:29:13,500 --> 00:29:15,670
Every time my period comes,
my stomach hurts.

697
00:29:21,500 --> 00:29:23,260
What medicine did you take? Let me see.

698
00:29:23,410 --> 00:29:26,100
(Acetaminophen Tablets,
Black-Boned Chicken Bai Feng Pills)

699
00:29:26,890 --> 00:29:28,910
These two medicines
shouldn't be taken together!

700
00:29:29,130 --> 00:29:30,299
I had no idea until I checked,

701
00:29:30,300 --> 00:29:31,830
but once I saw it, I was shocked.

702
00:29:32,100 --> 00:29:34,299
The TCM she usually takes

703
00:29:34,300 --> 00:29:35,299
and the painkiller

704
00:29:35,300 --> 00:29:37,019
can't be taken at the same time.

705
00:29:37,020 --> 00:29:38,520
Taking them can irritate the stomach.

706
00:29:38,560 --> 00:29:40,250
I don't know if her menstrual cramps

707
00:29:40,260 --> 00:29:43,209
are caused by poor blood circulation.

708
00:29:43,210 --> 00:29:45,700
So, she really shouldn't be
taking medicine randomly.

709
00:29:47,130 --> 00:29:49,260
I mean, seriously.
What would she do

710
00:29:49,450 --> 00:29:50,630
without me?

711
00:29:51,450 --> 00:29:53,870
You did an amazing job
this time, Huan'er.

712
00:29:54,860 --> 00:29:57,190
I, Qian Lina, raised a great daughter!

713
00:29:58,410 --> 00:29:59,339
I totally understand

714
00:29:59,340 --> 00:30:01,830
the sense of fulfillment you get
from helping others.

715
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:03,859
But listen, pharmacy

716
00:30:03,860 --> 00:30:06,110
isn't as simple as you think.

717
00:30:09,060 --> 00:30:10,150
We'll see about that.

718
00:30:11,020 --> 00:30:11,780
Alright.

719
00:30:11,820 --> 00:30:13,339
You really are my child.

720
00:30:13,340 --> 00:30:15,620
You acted just like me when I was young.
Wait right here.

721
00:30:22,060 --> 00:30:22,910
Here you go.

722
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:24,440
You want to study pharmacy, right?

723
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:26,580
(Compendium of Materia Medica)
First, read through this book.

724
00:30:26,580 --> 00:30:28,380
Then decide whether or not
you want to study pharmacy.

725
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,160
Mom!

726
00:30:29,170 --> 00:30:30,819
This is TCM.

727
00:30:30,820 --> 00:30:32,609
I want to study Western medicine.

728
00:30:32,610 --> 00:30:34,019
You need to first understand

729
00:30:34,020 --> 00:30:35,700
the stuff our ancestors left behind.

730
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:37,350
Then we can talk about Western medicine.

731
00:31:09,540 --> 00:31:10,680
(The day after tomorrow,)

732
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:12,840
(I will have a death match
versus the soccer academy.)

733
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:13,780
(Wait for my good news.)

734
00:31:21,740 --> 00:31:22,740
(All the best.)

735
00:31:30,130 --> 00:31:31,260
(Looking back,)

736
00:31:31,410 --> 00:31:33,129
(compared to other people,)

737
00:31:33,130 --> 00:31:34,259
(I wondered)

738
00:31:34,260 --> 00:31:35,929
(if this little goal of mine)

739
00:31:35,930 --> 00:31:37,500
(passes as a dream.)

740
00:31:40,170 --> 00:31:41,420
(Teaching material, key points)

741
00:31:43,890 --> 00:31:45,500
(Surgery)

742
00:31:54,890 --> 00:31:56,020
Jing Xichi.

743
00:31:56,580 --> 00:31:57,499
I'm fine, Mom.

744
00:31:57,500 --> 00:31:59,070
I dropped the ball.

745
00:32:04,100 --> 00:32:06,059
(Nevertheless, it's given me)

746
00:32:06,060 --> 00:32:09,350
(unprecedented peace of mind
and satisfaction.)

747
00:32:24,260 --> 00:32:25,260
Headed to school?

748
00:32:27,170 --> 00:32:28,150
Watching soccer, Dad?

749
00:32:29,260 --> 00:32:30,430
Barcelona.

750
00:32:33,540 --> 00:32:34,350
Dad,

751
00:32:35,610 --> 00:32:39,460
these are the tickets for today's match.

752
00:32:44,650 --> 00:32:45,830
For your mom and me?

753
00:32:47,020 --> 00:32:48,780
Are you trying to get me in trouble?

754
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:50,430
You asked me to keep this from her,

755
00:32:51,020 --> 00:32:53,339
and now you're exposing everything.

756
00:32:53,340 --> 00:32:54,300
Dad,

757
00:32:54,340 --> 00:32:56,590
I have to go to this match.

758
00:32:56,820 --> 00:32:58,689
The youth team coach will be there.

759
00:32:58,690 --> 00:32:59,449
Basically,

760
00:32:59,450 --> 00:33:01,110
he's coming to scout me.

761
00:33:01,170 --> 00:33:02,579
If I perform well,

762
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:04,460
he might let me join the youth team.

763
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:05,859
And if I get in,

764
00:33:05,860 --> 00:33:07,700
it'll be a huge help for my development.

765
00:33:07,780 --> 00:33:08,980
Plus, Dad, think about it.

766
00:33:10,020 --> 00:33:12,110
If I play really well

767
00:33:12,500 --> 00:33:13,689
and the coach likes me,

768
00:33:13,690 --> 00:33:15,240
he might put in a few good words for me.

769
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:16,680
That could make all the difference!

770
00:33:20,690 --> 00:33:21,780
I'll see what I can do.

771
00:33:22,740 --> 00:33:24,390
No matter if your mom goes or not,

772
00:33:25,500 --> 00:33:26,910
just do your best.

773
00:33:28,860 --> 00:33:29,739
Good luck, son.

774
00:33:29,740 --> 00:33:30,910
I'll leave the tickets here.

775
00:33:31,100 --> 00:33:31,940
Got to go.

776
00:33:39,290 --> 00:33:43,540
(Preliminary Match Entry Ticket)

777
00:33:53,130 --> 00:33:55,670
I wonder how Xichi's game is going...

778
00:33:57,520 --> 00:33:59,140
Jing Xichi from your class got injured.

779
00:33:59,140 --> 00:34:00,600
Hurry, come with me to the infirmary!

780
00:34:01,300 --> 00:34:02,739
No way. He got hurt?

781
00:34:02,740 --> 00:34:03,910
Jing Xichi is injured?

782
00:34:04,130 --> 00:34:05,020
What do we do?

783
00:34:12,410 --> 00:34:13,510
How is he?

784
00:34:14,340 --> 00:34:15,300
What happened?

785
00:34:15,450 --> 00:34:16,339
Two players collided.

786
00:34:16,340 --> 00:34:17,569
He got pinned underneath.

787
00:34:17,570 --> 00:34:18,740
He seemed fine when he got up,

788
00:34:18,740 --> 00:34:20,450
but after a few steps,
he suddenly collapsed.

789
00:34:20,450 --> 00:34:21,380
He can't even stand now.

790
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:23,020
He needs to get to the hospital ASAP.

791
00:34:23,220 --> 00:34:25,219
Go to the entrance
and flag down a taxi for us!

792
00:34:25,220 --> 00:34:26,049
Got it.

793
00:34:26,050 --> 00:34:27,760
Huan'er, help us get a leave of absence

794
00:34:27,780 --> 00:34:28,580
and take our bags.

795
00:34:29,930 --> 00:34:31,220
What happened?

796
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:33,420
I'll take you to the hospital.
Quick, quick.

797
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:34,360
Put him on my back!

798
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:34,990
Come on.

799
00:34:35,180 --> 00:34:35,900
Here.

800
00:34:35,940 --> 00:34:37,040
- Slowly does it.
- Slowly.

801
00:34:37,050 --> 00:34:38,260
- Slowly does it.
- Careful.

802
00:34:38,450 --> 00:34:39,260
Okay.

803
00:34:39,300 --> 00:34:39,659
Okay.

804
00:34:39,660 --> 00:34:40,259
Let's go.

805
00:34:40,260 --> 00:34:41,030
Go on.

806
00:34:41,970 --> 00:34:42,449
Go.

807
00:34:42,450 --> 00:34:43,260
Go.

808
00:34:58,970 --> 00:34:59,819
Where is he?

809
00:34:59,820 --> 00:35:00,900
What's the diagnosis?

810
00:35:01,010 --> 00:35:02,260
A hamstring injury.

811
00:35:02,300 --> 00:35:03,049
It's pretty bad.

812
00:35:03,050 --> 00:35:03,950
Is it that way?

813
00:35:04,410 --> 00:35:05,219
Huan'er,

814
00:35:05,220 --> 00:35:06,259
sit, sit down.

815
00:35:06,260 --> 00:35:07,009
Calm down.

816
00:35:07,010 --> 00:35:07,900
Take a seat.

817
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,360
Mr. and Mrs. Jing are inside.

818
00:35:09,370 --> 00:35:10,340
Let's wait here.

819
00:35:12,370 --> 00:35:14,150
Will he... need surgery?

820
00:35:14,520 --> 00:35:16,420
My dad recommended
conservative treatment.

821
00:35:16,740 --> 00:35:18,340
How long will it take to recover?

822
00:35:21,180 --> 00:35:22,700
The recovery period will take at least

823
00:35:22,860 --> 00:35:24,030
a few months.

824
00:35:34,490 --> 00:35:35,740
Mr. and Mrs. Jing...

825
00:35:37,490 --> 00:35:38,990
You guys need not worry.

826
00:35:39,050 --> 00:35:41,380
We should have confidence
in the patient at this time.

827
00:35:41,970 --> 00:35:43,110
Mrs. Jing,

828
00:35:43,370 --> 00:35:45,510
why are you the one comforting me?

829
00:35:46,370 --> 00:35:47,590
Occupational disease, I guess.

830
00:35:49,700 --> 00:35:50,590
Song Cong.

831
00:35:51,140 --> 00:35:52,190
Huan'er.

832
00:35:53,010 --> 00:35:55,420
Xichi wouldn't tell us anything.

833
00:35:55,570 --> 00:35:57,070
You're his close friends.

834
00:35:57,260 --> 00:35:58,740
Please talk to him for us.

835
00:36:01,340 --> 00:36:02,150
We will.

836
00:36:02,340 --> 00:36:03,420
Don't worry.

837
00:36:03,700 --> 00:36:05,699
Okay, it's getting late.

838
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:06,859
We'll be here.

839
00:36:06,860 --> 00:36:07,969
You guys can go home.

840
00:36:07,970 --> 00:36:09,510
You still have classes tomorrow.

841
00:36:10,410 --> 00:36:11,260
Then...

842
00:36:12,140 --> 00:36:14,470
Then we'll leave first.

843
00:36:37,940 --> 00:36:40,640
(Preliminary Match Entry Ticket)
Our boy asked me to give this to you.

844
00:36:41,530 --> 00:36:42,969
He said you might change your mind

845
00:36:42,970 --> 00:36:44,420
if you watched him play.

846
00:36:44,820 --> 00:36:46,070
I didn't give it to you.

847
00:36:47,450 --> 00:36:48,739
I reckon he went too hard

848
00:36:48,740 --> 00:36:49,900
and got injured.

849
00:36:51,300 --> 00:36:53,070
Anyway, back to the main point.

850
00:36:53,860 --> 00:36:55,740
What's so wrong

851
00:36:56,340 --> 00:36:57,590
about playing soccer?

852
00:36:59,180 --> 00:37:00,190
Jing.

853
00:37:00,820 --> 00:37:02,510
Don't you put up a front with me.

854
00:37:03,220 --> 00:37:04,739
Didn't we agree

855
00:37:04,740 --> 00:37:06,300
to stand on the same page?

856
00:37:07,010 --> 00:37:08,860
You said he's in a rebellious phase.

857
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:10,080
We should give him some room.

858
00:37:10,090 --> 00:37:12,030
I'll be the bad cop,
and you're the good cop.

859
00:37:12,050 --> 00:37:14,859
Sooner or later he will not
be able to handle it and give it up.

860
00:37:14,860 --> 00:37:15,569
Now what?

861
00:37:15,570 --> 00:37:17,299
You blame everything on me.
I'm responsible

862
00:37:17,300 --> 00:37:18,510
while you get a pass.

863
00:37:19,260 --> 00:37:20,779
I knew it.

864
00:37:20,780 --> 00:37:22,489
When you were being the good cop,

865
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:24,550
you... you had a different idea.

866
00:37:25,010 --> 00:37:26,670
Now you're going overboard.

867
00:37:26,740 --> 00:37:28,260
All I wanted was the best for our son.

868
00:37:28,380 --> 00:37:29,730
What's wrong with playing soccer?

869
00:37:29,740 --> 00:37:31,400
You wanted the best for him?
In what way?

870
00:37:31,420 --> 00:37:32,730
Is being bedridden

871
00:37:32,740 --> 00:37:33,900
the best for him?

872
00:37:35,010 --> 00:37:35,969
To be frank,

873
00:37:35,970 --> 00:37:37,300
I was giving you respect.

874
00:37:37,570 --> 00:37:39,089
I know you weren't able

875
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:40,659
to be a professional soccer player.

876
00:37:40,660 --> 00:37:41,779
That's why you forced

877
00:37:41,780 --> 00:37:43,950
your dream upon your son.

878
00:37:46,970 --> 00:37:48,819
I failed to go professional

879
00:37:48,820 --> 00:37:49,929
because your family thought

880
00:37:49,930 --> 00:37:51,740
there was no future in it.

881
00:37:51,970 --> 00:37:53,110
To put it bluntly,

882
00:37:53,410 --> 00:37:55,190
you despise soccer.

883
00:37:59,930 --> 00:38:01,220
Jing Liqiang.

884
00:38:02,300 --> 00:38:04,030
Where is your conscience?

885
00:38:04,140 --> 00:38:04,969
I despise it?

886
00:38:04,970 --> 00:38:06,960
If I despised it,
I wouldn't have married you!

887
00:38:07,010 --> 00:38:07,969
Fine, whatever.

888
00:38:07,970 --> 00:38:09,470
We'll never be on the same page!

889
00:38:22,930 --> 00:38:24,510
You're back, Huan'er?

890
00:38:32,370 --> 00:38:33,220
Mom.

891
00:38:34,490 --> 00:38:36,070
Tell me the truth

892
00:38:36,450 --> 00:38:37,990
about Jing Xichi's condition.

893
00:38:40,970 --> 00:38:42,070
Hard to say.

894
00:38:43,220 --> 00:38:45,820
Song Cong's dad said it's common.

895
00:38:46,180 --> 00:38:48,380
What does "common" mean?

896
00:38:49,700 --> 00:38:50,859
It is common

897
00:38:50,860 --> 00:38:53,780
when it comes to athletes like him

898
00:38:53,970 --> 00:38:55,659
who push their bodies to the limit.

899
00:38:55,660 --> 00:38:58,049
Look, he has a hamstring injury.

900
00:38:58,050 --> 00:38:59,339
He should recover swiftly,

901
00:38:59,340 --> 00:39:01,190
but there's a higher chance
of future injuries.

902
00:39:02,220 --> 00:39:03,049
It's hard to say

903
00:39:03,050 --> 00:39:04,680
if he could go back
to how he was before.

904
00:39:04,700 --> 00:39:06,659
That's why you should
care about your health.

905
00:39:06,660 --> 00:39:08,529
It's the foundation of all foundations.

906
00:39:08,530 --> 00:39:11,700
Even if one tiny part
of your body gives up,

907
00:39:12,620 --> 00:39:14,820
there's no use talking about
whatever dream

908
00:39:15,340 --> 00:39:16,780
you might have.

909
00:39:19,300 --> 00:39:20,260
That...

910
00:39:21,370 --> 00:39:23,340
That sounds pretty serious.

911
00:39:26,300 --> 00:39:27,630
It's up to his recovery.

912
00:39:27,820 --> 00:39:30,070
Maybe he'll recover well. Right?

913
00:39:31,570 --> 00:39:33,700
Okay, it's late.

914
00:39:33,940 --> 00:39:34,880
You should go to bed.

915
00:39:34,890 --> 00:39:36,150
You have classes tomorrow.

916
00:40:16,930 --> 00:40:18,619
(He has a hamstring injury.)

917
00:40:18,620 --> 00:40:19,969
(He should recover swiftly,)

918
00:40:19,970 --> 00:40:22,100
(but there's a higher chance
for future injuries.)

919
00:40:22,780 --> 00:40:23,569
(It's hard to say)

920
00:40:23,570 --> 00:40:25,540
(if he could go back
to how he was before.)

921
00:40:27,220 --> 00:40:28,380
(What about you?)

922
00:40:28,530 --> 00:40:30,300
Do you want to play soccer?

923
00:40:31,140 --> 00:40:32,220
I guess.

924
00:40:32,860 --> 00:40:34,820
You really think I can't support myself?

925
00:40:34,920 --> 00:40:36,400
I want to get into Sports University

926
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:37,860
because it's my dream to play soccer.

927
00:40:37,860 --> 00:40:39,700
I get my goal in roundabout way.

928
00:40:39,860 --> 00:40:41,619
I'm going to represent our school

929
00:40:41,620 --> 00:40:43,659
in the inter-high school soccer league.

930
00:40:43,660 --> 00:40:45,009
That's awesome.

931
00:40:45,010 --> 00:40:46,780
It's your chance
to make the school proud.

932
00:40:46,780 --> 00:40:47,950
Of course.

933
00:40:58,700 --> 00:41:00,070
(Are you alright?)

934
00:41:11,650 --> 00:41:12,809
(Are you alright?)

935
00:41:12,810 --> 00:41:16,929
(Send to Piggy Jing)

936
00:41:16,930 --> 00:41:18,369
(Send a message to Piggy Jing)

937
00:41:18,370 --> 00:41:19,980
(Sending)

938
00:41:21,340 --> 00:41:23,529
(There's no way for me to know)

939
00:41:23,530 --> 00:41:26,070
(how it feels when a soccer fanatic)

940
00:41:26,530 --> 00:41:29,340
(injured his leg.)

941
00:41:31,450 --> 00:41:34,820
(Mom's words keep circling in my head.)

942
00:41:35,860 --> 00:41:39,300
(Dreams seem brilliant)

943
00:41:39,700 --> 00:41:42,470
(but are actually so fragile.)

944
00:41:43,050 --> 00:41:46,550
(When a tiny part
in your body breaks down,)

945
00:41:46,740 --> 00:41:49,510
(it could mark the end of a dream.)

946
00:41:50,530 --> 00:41:52,260
(No matter how hard you try,)

947
00:41:52,530 --> 00:41:54,030
(how persistent you are,)

948
00:41:54,340 --> 00:41:55,740
(and how much passion you have,)

949
00:41:56,970 --> 00:41:58,780
(it is all futile.)

950
00:42:02,010 --> 00:42:03,380
(Are you alright?)

951
00:42:37,320 --> 00:42:42,490
♪Fallen leaves flutter past your gaze♪

952
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:49,360
♪I dream of worlds within your days♪

953
00:42:51,130 --> 00:42:56,480
♪Countless times,
I write your name in my heart♪

954
00:42:56,790 --> 00:43:02,280
♪Wishes whispered to the stars above♪

955
00:43:04,870 --> 00:43:09,890
♪How many faces in the glass I see♪

956
00:43:11,680 --> 00:43:16,920
♪Time's gentle hand
pulling me out of my cocoon♪

957
00:43:18,520 --> 00:43:23,940
♪Under the sun,
a rainbow butterfly takes flight♪

958
00:43:24,400 --> 00:43:29,900
♪To rest upon your left shoulder bright♪

959
00:43:31,100 --> 00:43:35,060
♪I still hear your promise in my ears♪

960
00:43:35,060 --> 00:43:40,050
♪Before we said goodbye,
your spirit free♪

961
00:43:40,180 --> 00:43:43,610
♪And full of life♪

962
00:43:44,900 --> 00:43:48,360
♪If summer could last a little longer♪

963
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:53,470
♪Would regrets rewrite
where we'd gone wrong?♪

964
00:43:53,730 --> 00:43:58,120
♪And let me be there with you
at the end of the story♪

965
00:43:58,620 --> 00:44:02,520
♪Watching your silhouette from behind♪

966
00:44:02,520 --> 00:44:07,460
♪My footsteps slow, we were too young♪

967
00:44:07,460 --> 00:44:10,250
♪To know right from wrong♪

968
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:15,690
♪Your sweat-kissed face
I hold in my memory♪

969
00:44:15,690 --> 00:44:18,940
♪Glows as bright as ever♪

970
00:44:19,100 --> 00:44:24,860
♪I hope one day we'll meet again♪

971
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:29,880
♪At just the right time♪
